Orders, Medals and Certificates of Honorary Titles Awarded to Kim Jong Il on Display 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 21 (KCNA) -- The orders, medals and certificates of honorary titles leader Kim Jong Il received from different countries and international organizations have been comprehensively displayed at the International Friendship Exhibition on the occasion of the 40th anniversary of his start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 On display at the International Friendship Exhibition in a chronological order are nearly 400 orders, medals and certificates of honorary titles awarded to him by political parties, states, governments, parliaments, establishments, organizations and international organizations in the last more than two decades since the 1980s. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Exhibited there are orders, medals and academic degrees, certificates of honorary titles and medals of various fields including philosophy, politics, sociology, economics and pedagogy conferred upon him by many countries, regions and international organizations in high recognition of his outstanding political qualification and extraordinary leadership ability in the 1980s. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Orders, medals and certificates of honorary titles awarded to him include certificates of honorary leaders and honorary chairmen conferred upon him by different political parties with boundless reverence and absolute trust in him who has defended the destiny of socialism with his great Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "Kiettikhoun Order" of Laos, "Order of Great Cross" of Niger, "Republic Order of Necklace" of Egypt, "Great Order of Independence" of Equatorial Guinea, "Order of Democracy" of Colombia and other highest orders awarded to him by different countries clearly prove his high international prestige and noble personality as a great man. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also displayed there are orders, medals and certificates of honorary titles awarded to him on more than 50 occasions in celebration of his birthday in February, the significant international holiday common to humankind. They include "Gold Star Order of Peace" of Mongolia, Marshal Zhukov Medal of Russia, certificate of honorary leader of the People's Party of Costa Rica, certificate of honorary citizen of Kampala City of Uganda, certificates of honorary academician and doctor of the International IT Academy and certificate and medal of honorary professor of Chiclayo University of Peru  Also seen there are certificate of "Special Guest," the highest title of Cavdare City of Lara State of Venezuela, awarded to him though it is the practice to present it only to prominent figures who personally visited the city, and the medal and certificate of the Moscow Committee of War Veterans conferred upon him for the first time since its institution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the exhibits are the Russian medal "The 50th anniversary of the victory in the great Patriotic War (1941-1945)," the Portuguese medal marking the 500th anniversary of the discovery of the continent, the medal commemorating the 125th anniversary of the International Telecommunication Union, certificates of honorary citizens and honorary guests of honor awarded to him by famous cities of different countries, certificates of honorary academicians, professors and doctors presented to him by scores of well-known universities and scientific research institutions. They reflect the desire of the world progressives to hand down his exploits forever together with their commemoration days.

40th Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Start of Work Observed Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 21 (KCNA) -- Celebration meetings, round-table talks and explanation meetings were held by the Revolutionary Socialist Party of Peru, the Revolutionary Communist Party of Britain (Marxist-Leninist) and the Socialist Unionist Party of Syria, in Rome of Italy, Basel of Switzerland and at a company of Indonesia from June 11 to 13 on the occasion of the 40th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea (WPK).
 The general secretary of the Revolutionary Socialist Party of Peru and other Peruvian political party leaders in their speeches at a meeting said the WPK could be strengthened into a powerful and dignified invincible party entirely thanks to the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il and, under his Songun policy, the Korean People's Army and people with their united strength were bravely countering the U.S. styling itself the "only superpower" in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The president of the Group of Dialectical Materialists of Italy said at a meeting that the socialist cause and the cause of Korea's reunification pioneered by President Kim Il Sung were being successfully carried forward by Kim Jong Il with his clairvoyance and iron will. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general secretary of the Socialist Unionist Party of Syria in his speech at a round-table talk stressed that under Kim Jong Il's leadership the WPK and the Korean people were advancing today in the van of the anti-imperialist struggle, adhering to the steadfast principle and brave stand against the U.S. arbitrariness and vicious maneuvers of aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Congratulatory messages and letters to Kim Jong Il were adopted at the meetings.

Korean People's Struggle for Reunification Supported 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 21 (KCNA) -- J. K. Patel, director of the Indian Institute for the Foreign Policy, made public a statement on June 13 on the occasion of the 4th anniversary of the publication of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration.
 We express support to and solidarity with the Korean people in their struggle to achieve the independent reunification of the country, he stated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the June 15 joint declaration carries the steadfast will of leader Kim Jong Il to reunify the country as President Kim Il Sung, wished, he said dramatic developments have been witnessed in the movement for the reunification of Korea under the independent and all-embracing policy of Kim Jong Il and under his distinguished leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The June 15 joint declaration is a historic document which displayed all over the world the will of the Korean nation to solve the issue of reunification independently. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 However, the U.S. administration which dislikes the unity and reunification of the Korean nation is disturbing the implementation of the joint declaration, clinging to its hostile policy towards the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No force on earth can block the vigorous advance of the Korean nation to achieve the independent reunification under the banner of the historic June 15 joint declaration and the cause of Korea's reunification will certainly be achieved in the near future, he stressed.

U.S.Unilateral Pressure for DPRK's Dismantlement of Its "Nuclear Program" Blasted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 21 (KCNA) -- As already reported the G-8 summit recently held in the United States adopted a "G-8 action plan on nonproliferation" which contains paragraphs demanding the DPRK accept CVID, asserting that its possession of nuclear deterrent is a violation of the international obligation.
 Rodong Sinmun Monday in a signed commentary says that this was prompted by the U.S. intention to force its unilateral will upon the DPRK in violation of the principle of justice, equality and impartiality in international relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is chiefly to blame for the emergence of the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the U.S. which reneged on its international obligation and wantonly violated the NPT. It should, therefore, dismantle nukes in a verifiable and irreversible manner. But the "advanced countries" kept mum about the U.S. nuclear-related crimes at the summit. By faking up such a document the U.S. and other countries sought to put pressure upon the DPRK to scrap its nuclear program first through "forced inspection" in a bid to stifle it as they did in Iraq. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The paragraphs of the "document" dealing with the issue of the DPRK only provide with the DPRK ample justification to increase its defensive nuclear deterrent force with powerful catalyst. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For a fair solution to the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. the countries concerned should demand the U.S. drop at once its hostile policy toward the DPRK proceeding from a correct standpoint and attitude  The DPRK does not have any interest in other option but this nor expects it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. seems to claim that it alone has the "political vision" and "standards" to discern between right and wrong and can do everything and other countries should meekly follow its will. Such U.S.-style superpower logic and unilateralism will never work on the DPRK.

Rodong Sinmun on Kim Jong Il's Leadership Exploits 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 21 (KCNA) -- The leadership exploits of Kim Jong Il provide a sure guarantee for dynamically advancing the revolutionary cause of Juche and successfully accomplishing it, says Rodong Sinmun Monday in a signed article. It goes on:
The valuable ideological and theoretical boon provided by Kim Jong Il serves as guidelines for all fields of the revolution and construction. This provides a decisive guarantee for victoriously advancing the Juche revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has given lucid answers to all the issues arising in all fields ranging from philosophy and political economy to literature and art and from the party, state and army building to the issue of accomplishing the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean-style socialism is most advantageous as political, economic, cultural and all other fabrics of social life under it are efflorescing and the DPRK is vigorously advancing along the orbit of independence. This true picture clearly testifies to the fact that its revolution is sure to triumph at all times thanks to this great ideological and theoretical boon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The tradition and experience gained by him in leading the work in all fields and at all units provide a reliable foundation for bringing about surges in the revolution and construction without let-up. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has wisely led the overall party, state and army affairs since he started working at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea and performed valuable exploits, established a good tradition and accumulated a wealth of experience for effecting a steady surge in the revolutionary cause of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The shining exploits, experience and valuable tradition provided by Kim Jong Il while directly leading the work in different domains in the 1970s in particular, demonstrated their tremendous vitality in the practice of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il made a new history of building a great prosperous powerful nation with the might of Songun, giving a sure guarantee for accomplishing the revolutionary cause of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The military power for self defense of the DPRK has been increased in every way despite the U.S. imperialists' recent continued moves to isolate and stifle it and a breakthrough was made towards building a great prosperous powerful nation. This stirring reality fully demonstrates the might of Kim Jong Il's Songun leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A turning phase brought about in the efforts to accomplish the Korean people's cause of national reunification and the unprecedentedly high international prestige of the DPRK represent a shining victory of Kim Jong Il's Songun politics.

Pyongyang-Dandong International Bus Service Starts 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 21 (KCNA) -- A regular international bus service between Pyongyang and Dandong, China, has started.
 The first batch of buses left Changgwangsan Hotel in Pyongyang for Dandong at 8 a.m. on June 21. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 From June 22, buses will leave Pyongyang and Dandong simultaneously. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bus service is available every day except Saturday and Sunday.  The buses offer necessary service and comfort to travelers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bus line is operated by the Korea Ulrim Transportation Joint Venture Company and the Dandong, China, International Tourist Agency.

Kimjongilia Show Goes on Successfully
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 21 (KCNA) -- The Kimjongilia show, which opened in Pyongyang in celebration of the 40th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea (June 19), is going on successfully.
 On display there are more than 15,000 Kimjongilia pots exhibited by 74 ministries, national institutions and armed forces units. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attracting particular attention of the visitors are the stands of servicemen which reflect their loyalty to Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Conspicuous on the stand of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces is a portrait of Kim Jong Il against the background of the building of the WPK Central Committee and the blue sky over the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It represents two red flags with two rotating crystal pots of Kimilsungia and some 610 Kimjongilia pots. It shows the strong will of the servicemen to win victory after victory under the leadership of Kim Jong Il, holding high the red flag on this land where the revolutionary history of President Kim Il Sung is being successfully carried forward. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The stand is decorated by a small fountain. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Marvelous is the stand of Ri Sang Ryol's unit of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It also presents 610 Kimjongilia pots portraying a flying flag bearing Kim Jong Il's portrait and, in its lower part, the building of the Party Central Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Another stand, which is flanked by a model of Jong Il Peak made with pumice stones of Mt. Paektu and a model of   Kim Il Sung University made with various kinds of flowers, vividly shows Kim Jong Il's great life and exploits performed for the Party building. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Mansudae Art Studio's stand with 19 hexangular supporters represents beautiful Kimjongilia with blue leaves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The stand of the Bureau of Reception for Overseas Compatriots portrays a floral basket with Kimjongilia pots reflecting the people's best wishes to him who has been leading the WPK along the road of victory without any slightest deviation over the past 40 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The show is full of ardent will of the Korean people to carry out the revolutionary cause under Kim Jong Il's leadership.

Korean Wrestling Tournament for "Grand Bull Prize" under Way
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 21 (KCNA) -- The second round of the "Grand Bull Price" National TV Korean Wrestling (Ssirum) Tournament of Working People on the occasion of the lunar May 5th, a folk holiday, is going on at Pyongyang Indoor Stadium amid public interest.
 At the tournament, which began on the 20th of June, 60 players selected in provincial (city) matches competed in an open-weight and knock-out way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Competing at the matches held on the 21st were the 30 selected players and Ri Jong Chol of North Phyongan Province who distinguished himself in the first round of the tournament. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Players from Pyongyang and North Phyongan and North Hamgyong provinces proved successful at the second day matches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fans raised cheers rocking the stadium, dancing mask dance and other dances whenever players showed wonderful techniques. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The matches of those above sixty also took place amid a thunderous hand-clapping of the spectators. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The tournament continues.

KCNA Assails Japan's New Laws for Militarization and Overseas Invasion
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 21 (KCNA) -- Seven laws related to emergency and a bill banning the portcall of specified foreign ships were adopted at the session of the House of Councilors of Japan on June 14.
 This merits serious attention as it is a provocative act of destabilizing peace and stability of Asia and seriously infringing upon the sovereignty of the DPRK in particular. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese right-wing conservative forces adopted three laws related to emergency last year including the law for coping with armed attack. The recent adoption of the seven laws finally brought to completion the adjustment of the laws related to emergency aimed at providing a legal and institutional guarantee for their revival of militarism and reinvasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 By adopting the seven laws the Japanese right-wing conservative forces have strengthened Japan's military alliance with the U.S. and paved a wide avenue for overseas aggression. This has reduced to a dead document the "Peace Constitution" which bans Japan's exercise of the right to collective self-defence and the right of belligerency. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese right-wing conservatives have become more undisguised recently in their moves to institute a new constitution aimed at the revival of militarism and overseas expansion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is clearly proved by the fact that the Liberal Democratic Party of Japan included "the institution of the new constitution" in the draft amendment to be made to its "programme" on the occasion of its 50th founding anniversary which will fall on November 2005 and set forth the constitutional revision as its supreme task. They call for deleting paragraph 2 of article 9, a core article of the "Peace Constitution", which bans Japan's possession of armed forces, defining the "Self-Defence Forces" as an army and claiming the right to self-defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In fact, for the Japanese aggression forces the "Peace Constitution" has been a stumbling block in their way of legislating on the militarization of the state system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Therefore, the right-wing conservatives of Japan have so far rendered the constitution defunct little by little and have already declared the areas around the Korean peninsula as the theatre of their operation under the pretext of coping with emergency in its surrounding areas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What matters is that they have chosen the DPRK as the target of their constitutional revision. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The final adoption of the law banning the portcall of specified foreign ships is aimed to strangle the DPRK economically. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With nothing can the Japanese right-wing conservative forces justify their unsavory acts of going against the positive trend towards the improved relations between the DPRK and Japan noticeable in the wake of the talks between the top leaders of the two countries on May 22. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The right-wing conservatives of Japan should not run wild, well aware that Japan's revival of militarism and overseas expansion will only lead it to its self-destruction.
